gr.agroscape.agents.expectations

Class AbstractExpectation<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • gr.agroscape.agents.expectations.AbstractExpectation<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the Value
    K - the Key
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ExpectedCropPrices, ExpectedPlotCropVarCost, ExpectedPlotCropYield

    public abstract class AbstractExpectation<K,V>
extends java.lang.Object
    An abstract class for an Expectation.
    An Expectation has the form of Key->Value and those two can be of any type.
    For example a "Crop Prices" expectation is of the form Crop->Long.

    There are two ways to instantiate an object: Either by giving explicitly the K->V pairs, or by giving only the K values and implicitly assigning the default values to them.

    In order to subclass, an override implementation of getDefaultValues is necessary.
    Author:
    jkr
